Setup
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

- turn on websocket support in conf/gateway-site.xml 
- make sure the following service is in conf/topology/sandbox.xml
<service>
   <role>WEBSHELLUI</role>
   <url>http://localhost:4242</url>
  </service>
  <service>
   <role>WEBSHELLWS</role>
   <url>ws://localhost:4242/webshellws</url>
  </service>
- restart server (kill running servers then run 'ant start-test-servers')
- start webshell server (implementation in gateway-service-webshell/)
- use firefox to access: https://localhost:8443/gateway/sandbox/webshellui 
(safari gives WebSocket network error: OSStatus Error -9807: Invalid certificate chain )
6:31
some notes:
- i chose port 4242 to run the webshell server, if yours is in use, can change it in application.yml (also change the port in sandbox.xml)
- right now my webshell server only works when proxied through knox, because i’ve hardcoded the websocket endpoint as ‘wss://localhost:8443/gateway/sandbox/webshellws’ (in js/webssh.js line 31) 
- the web shell would ssh into the sandbox i have running on a local vm. but you can change to whatever you want to ssh into (in page/webssh.html line 31:35)
6:33
these hardcoded parts i will later modify them once we are more clear on what we wanna do
6:35
in addition , it does support multiple browser connections. and each with its own ssh session, but all to the same host:port

